## Core SDK

The SDK itself is a library — there's nothing to deploy. Install it in your project:

```bash
npm install @nirholas/pump-sdk @solana/web3.js @coral-xyz/anchor bn.js
```

---

## Telegram Bot

Interactive Telegram bot for monitoring PumpFun fee claims, token launches, graduations, whale trades, and fee distributions. Supports individual DM and group chat interactions with `/watch`, `/unwatch`, `/list` commands and an optional REST API with webhooks and SSE.

**Platform:** Railway (recommended), Docker, or any Node.js host  
**Port:** 3000  
**Health Check:** `GET /api/v1/health`  
**Persistent Storage:** `/app/data` (watch entries)

### Railway Deployment

```bash
cd telegram-bot
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your values

railway login
railway init
railway up
```

The `railway.json` configures the Dockerfile builder, V2 runtime, `ON_FAILURE` restart policy (10 retries), and healthcheck at `/api/v1/health`.

> **Volumes:** Railway bans the `VOLUME` keyword in Dockerfiles. Use [Railway Volumes](https://docs.railway.com/reference/volumes) to persist `/app/data`.

### Docker Deployment

```bash
cd telegram-bot
docker build -t pump-telegram-bot .
docker run -d \
  --name pump-telegram-bot \
  --restart unless-stopped \
  -p 3000:3000 \
  --env-file .env \
  -v telegram-bot-data:/app/data \
  pump-telegram-bot
```

The multi-stage Dockerfile uses `node:20-alpine`, creates a non-root `bot:bot` user, and includes a built-in healthcheck.

### Node.js Deployment

```bash
cd telegram-bot
npm install
npm run build
cp .env.example .env  # edit with your values
node dist/index.js
```

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|----------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` | ✅ | — | Token from [@BotFather](https://t.me/BotFather) |
| `SOLANA_RPC_URL` | ✅ | — | Solana RPC endpoint (mainnet recommended) |
| `SOLANA_WS_URL` | ⬜ | Derived from RPC | WebSocket URL for real-time monitoring |
| `ALLOWED_USER_IDS` | ⬜ | — | Comma-separated Telegram user IDs to allow |
| `POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS` | ⬜ | `15` | Polling interval when WebSocket unavailable |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | ⬜ | `info` | `debug` \| `info` \| `warn` \| `error` |
| `ENABLE_LAUNCH_MONITOR` | ⬜ | `false` | Enable new token launch monitoring |
| `GITHUB_ONLY_FILTER` | ⬜ | `false` | Only notify for GitHub-linked tokens |
| `IPFS_GATEWAY` | ⬜ | `https://cf-ipfs.com/ipfs/` | IPFS gateway for token metadata |
| `ENABLE_API` | ⬜ | `false` | Enable the REST API server |
| `API_ONLY` | ⬜ | `false` | Run API without Telegram bot |
| `API_PORT` | ⬜ | `3000` | HTTP port for the API server |
| `API_KEYS` | ⬜ | — | Comma-separated API keys for authentication |
| `WEBHOOK_SECRET` | ⬜ | — | HMAC-SHA256 secret for webhook signatures |
| `CORS_ORIGINS` | ⬜ | `*` | CORS allowed origins |
| `MAX_WATCHES_PER_CLIENT` | ⬜ | `100` | Max watches per API client |
| `RATE_LIMIT_MAX` | ⬜ | `100` | Max requests per rate limit window |
| `RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS` | ⬜ | `60000` | Rate limit window duration (ms) |
| `CLAIM_BUFFER_SIZE` | ⬜ | `10000` | Max claim events buffered in memory |
| `ENABLE_GRADUATION_ALERTS` | ⬜ | `true` | Enable graduation/migration alerts |
| `ENABLE_TRADE_ALERTS` | ⬜ | `false` | Enable whale trade alerts |
| `WHALE_THRESHOLD_SOL` | ⬜ | `10` | Minimum SOL for whale alert |
| `ENABLE_FEE_DISTRIBUTION_ALERTS` | ⬜ | `false` | Enable creator fee distribution alerts |

### Verification

```bash
# Health check
curl http://localhost:3000/api/v1/health

# Verify bot is responding
curl -s "https://api.telegram.org/bot${TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}/getMe"
```

