## Claim Bot

Interactive Telegram bot for tracking PumpFun fee claims across Pump, PumpSwap, and PumpFees programs. Monitors both token contracts and X handles with optional Twitter follower tracking and influencer detection.

**Platform:** Railway (recommended), Docker  
**Port:** None (bot only, no HTTP server)  
**Persistent Storage:** `/app/data`

### Railway Deployment

```bash
cd claim-bot
cp .env.example .env
railway login && railway init && railway up
```

### Docker Deployment

```bash
cd claim-bot
docker build -t pump-claim-bot .
docker run -d \
  --name pump-claim-bot \
  --restart unless-stopped \
  --env-file .env \
  -v claim-bot-data:/app/data \
  pump-claim-bot
```

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|----------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` | ✅ | — | Token from @BotFather |
| `SOLANA_RPC_URL` | ✅ | — | Solana RPC HTTP URL (mainnet-beta) |
| `SOLANA_WS_URL` | ⬜ | Derived from RPC | WebSocket URL for real-time monitoring |
| `SOLANA_RPC_URLS` | ⬜ | — | Comma-separated fallback RPCs |
| `POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS` | ⬜ | `15` | Polling interval |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | ⬜ | `info` | `debug` \| `info` \| `warn` \| `error` |
| `TWITTER_BEARER_TOKEN` | ⬜ | — | Twitter API bearer token for follower tracking |
| `TWITTER_INFLUENCER_IDS` | ⬜ | — | Comma-separated influential X account IDs |

