## Outsiders Bot

Call-tracking Telegram bot with leaderboards, PNL cards, and performance analytics. Uses SQLite for persistence and canvas for image generation. Supports multi-chain (Solana, Ethereum, Base, BSC).

**Platform:** Any Node.js host (no Dockerfile provided)  
**Port:** None (bot only)  
**Persistent Storage:** SQLite database file

### Node.js Deployment

```bash
cd outsiders-bot
npm install
npm run build
cp .env.example .env  # edit with your values
node dist/index.js
```

### Docker Deployment (manual)

Since no Dockerfile is provided, you can use a generic Node.js container:

```bash
cd outsiders-bot
docker run -d \
  --name outsiders-bot \
  --restart unless-stopped \
  -v outsiders-data:/app/data \
  -w /app \
  -e TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_token \
  node:20-alpine sh -c "npm install && npm run build && node dist/index.js"
```

> **Note:** The `canvas` dependency requires native libraries. On Alpine, install `cairo-dev pango-dev jpeg-dev giflib-dev` first.

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|----------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` | ✅ | — | Token from @BotFather |
| `CALL_CHANNEL_ID` | ⬜ | — | Forward calls to a channel (numeric ID) |
| `DEXSCREENER_API` | ⬜ | `https://api.dexscreener.com` | DexScreener API base URL |
| `ATH_POLL_INTERVAL` | ⬜ | `60` | ATH polling interval in seconds |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | ⬜ | `info` | `debug` \| `info` \| `warn` \| `error` |
| `DB_PATH` | ⬜ | `./outsiders.db` | SQLite database path |

---

## Swarm Bot

Multi-strategy PumpFun trading bot with real-time web dashboard, SQLite persistence, and WebSocket-based position tracking. Uses the core Pump SDK for on-chain operations.

**Platform:** Docker (recommended), Railway, Node.js  
**Port:** 3100  
**Persistent Storage:** `/app/data/swarm.db` (SQLite)

### Docker Deployment

```bash
# Must be run from repo root (swarm-bot depends on root SDK)
docker build -t pump-swarm-bot -f swarm-bot/Dockerfile .
docker run -d \
  --name pump-swarm-bot \
  --restart unless-stopped \
  -p 3100:3100 \
  --env-file swarm-bot/.env \
  -v swarm-bot-data:/app/data \
  pump-swarm-bot
```

> **Important:** The swarm-bot Dockerfile copies the root SDK (`package.json`, `src/`, `tsconfig.json`, `tsup.config.ts`) because it depends on `@nirholas/pump-sdk` as a `file:..` dependency. Build from the repo root.

### Railway Deployment

```bash
cd swarm-bot
cp .env.example .env
railway login && railway init && railway up
```

The `railway.json` configures the Dockerfile builder with V2 runtime and `ON_FAILURE` restart.

### Node.js Deployment

```bash
# Build root SDK first
npm install && npm run build

cd swarm-bot
npm install
npm run build
cp .env.example .env  # edit with your values
node dist/index.js
```

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|----------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `SOLANA_RPC_URL` | ✅ | — | Solana RPC endpoint |
| `PORT` | ⬜ | `3100` | API server port |
| `DB_PATH` | ⬜ | `./data/swarm.db` | SQLite database path |
| `DEFAULT_SLIPPAGE_BPS` | ⬜ | `500` | Default slippage in basis points (500 = 5%) |
| `MAX_POSITION_SOL_PER_BOT` | ⬜ | `5` | Maximum SOL per bot position |
| `MAX_TOTAL_POSITION_SOL` | ⬜ | `50` | Maximum total SOL across all bots |
| `POLL_INTERVAL_MS` | ⬜ | `5000` | Feed poll interval (ms) |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | ⬜ | `info` | `debug` \| `info` \| `warn` \| `error` |

---

## Swarm Orchestrator

Bot orchestration layer with cross-bot event bus, fleet management, and admin dashboard. Manages lifecycle (start/stop/restart/build/logs) of all bots in the swarm via REST API and WebSocket.

**Platform:** Any Node.js host  
**Port:** 4000  
**Dependencies:** Individual bot services must be installed alongside

### Deployment

```bash
cd swarm
npm install
npm run build
cp .env.example .env  # edit with your values
node dist/index.js
```

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|----------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `SWARM_PORT` | ⬜ | `4000` | HTTP/WS server port |
| `SWARM_LOG_LEVEL` | ⬜ | `info` | Log level |
| `SWARM_HEALTH_INTERVAL` | ⬜ | `10000` | Health check interval (ms) |
| `SWARM_MAX_EVENTS` | ⬜ | `5000` | Max events buffered in memory |
| `SWARM_API_KEY` | ⬜ | — | API key for REST endpoint auth |
| `SWARM_CORS_ORIGINS` | ⬜ | `*` | CORS allowed origins |
| `SWARM_AUTO_START` | ⬜ | — | Comma-separated bot IDs to auto-start (e.g., `websocket-server,telegram-bot`) |

### REST API

```bash
# List all bots
curl http://localhost:4000/api/bots

# Start a bot
curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/api/bots/telegram-bot/start

# Stop a bot
curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/api/bots/telegram-bot/stop

# Aggregate metrics
curl http://localhost:4000/api/metrics
```

---

## Dashboard

Unified web control panel for monitoring and managing all bots in the swarm. Displays health status, metrics, and provides direct bot control.

**Platform:** Any Node.js host  
**Port:** 8080

### Deployment

```bash
cd dashboard
npm install
npm run build
cp .env.example .env  # edit with your values
node dist/server.js
```

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|----------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `DASHBOARD_PORT` | ⬜ | `8080` | HTTP server port |
| `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` | ⬜ | — | API key for dashboard authentication |
| `TELEGRAM_BOT_URL` | ⬜ | — | URL to Telegram Bot service |
| `CHANNEL_BOT_URL` | ⬜ | — | URL to Channel Bot service |
| `OUTSIDERS_BOT_URL` | ⬜ | — | URL to Outsiders Bot service |
| `WEBSOCKET_SERVER_URL` | ⬜ | — | URL to WebSocket Relay service |
| `TELEGRAM_BOT_API_KEY` | ⬜ | — | Telegram Bot API key for direct control |
| `TELEGRAM_BOT_ENABLE_API` | ⬜ | `true` | Enable Telegram Bot API integration |
| `SOLANA_RPC_URL` | ⬜ | `https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com` | Solana RPC endpoint |
| `SOLANA_RPC_URLS` | ⬜ | Derived from `SOLANA_RPC_URL` | Comma-separated fallback RPCs |

> **Tip:** Only set the `*_URL` variables for bots you actually run. The dashboard dynamically registers/monitors services based on which URLs are configured.

