## WebSocket Relay Server

Real-time token launch and fee claim broadcasting via WebSocket. Includes a built-in dashboard UI. Dual source: PumpFun API (primary) + Solana RPC (bonus data).

**Platform:** Railway (recommended), Fly.io, Render, or any host with WebSocket support  
**Port:** 3099  
**Health Check:** `GET /health`

### Railway Deployment

```bash
cd websocket-server
cp .env.example .env
railway login && railway init && railway up
```

The `railway.json` configures the start command (`node dist/server.js`), healthcheck at `/health`, and default environment variables.

### Docker Deployment

```bash
cd websocket-server
docker build -t pump-ws-relay .
docker run -d \
  --name pump-ws-relay \
  --restart unless-stopped \
  -p 3099:3099 \
  --env-file .env \
  pump-ws-relay
```

> **Note:** The websocket-server Dockerfile uses a single-stage build with `node:22-alpine` and includes the `public/` directory for the built-in dashboard UI.

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|----------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `PORT` | ⬜ | `3099` | HTTP/WS listen port |
| `SOLANA_RPC_WS` | ⬜ | `wss://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com` | Solana WebSocket URL for monitoring |
| `SOLANA_RPC_URL` | ⬜ | `https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com` | Solana HTTP RPC URL |
| `IPFS_GATEWAY` | ⬜ | `https://cf-ipfs.com/ipfs/` | IPFS gateway for metadata (must end with `/`) |
| `ENABLE_CLAIMS` | ⬜ | `true` | Enable fee claim monitoring |
| `CLAIM_POLL_INTERVAL` | ⬜ | `15000` | Claim poll interval (ms) |

### Verification

```bash
# Health check
curl http://localhost:3099/health

# WebSocket test (requires wscat: npm i -g wscat)
wscat -c ws://localhost:3099
```

### Scaling

The WebSocket relay handles ~10K concurrent connections on a 1 vCPU machine. For more, put behind a load balancer with **sticky sessions** (WebSocket connections are stateful).

