## MCP Server

Model Context Protocol server providing 55 tools, 4 resources, and 5 prompts for AI agent integration. Runs as a CLI tool embedded in host applications — not as a standalone deployed service.

**Platform:** CLI tool (stdio transport)  
**Install:** Via npm or local build

### Claude Desktop

Add to `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json` (macOS) or `%APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json` (Windows):

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "pump-sdk": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["/path/to/pump-fun-sdk/mcp-server/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "SOLANA_RPC_URL": "https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### VS Code / Cursor

Add to `.vscode/mcp.json` or project-level MCP config:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "pump-sdk": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": ["./mcp-server/dist/index.js"],
      "env": {
        "SOLANA_RPC_URL": "https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Build from Source

```bash
cd mcp-server
npm install
npm run build
# Test locally
node dist/index.js
```

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|----------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `SOLANA_RPC_URL` | ⬜ | `https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com` | Solana HTTP RPC endpoint |
| `SOLANA_RPC_URLS` | ⬜ | Derived from `SOLANA_RPC_URL` | Comma-separated RPC endpoints for failover |

> **Lazy RPC:** The MCP server only creates Solana connections when tools that need them are called. No RPC traffic at idle.

