## Production Checklist

### Before Going Live

- [ ] **RPC endpoint:** Use a paid provider (Helius, Alchemy, QuickNode) — public endpoints have strict rate limits
- [ ] **Environment variables:** All secrets set via env vars, never hardcoded
- [ ] **Bot tokens:** Generated fresh, not shared between environments (dev/staging/prod)
- [ ] **HTTPS:** All public endpoints served over TLS
- [ ] **Rate limiting:** REST API rate limits configured (`RATE_LIMIT_MAX`, `RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS`)
- [ ] **CORS:** Origins restricted to known domains (`CORS_ORIGINS`), not `*` in production
- [ ] **API keys:** Set `API_KEYS` for authenticated endpoints, `SWARM_API_KEY` for orchestrator
- [ ] **Monitoring:** Health check endpoints monitored (UptimeRobot, Betterstack, etc.)
- [ ] **Logging:** Structured logging enabled (`LOG_LEVEL=info`), no PII or private keys in logs
- [ ] **Restart policy:** `--restart unless-stopped` for Docker, `ON_FAILURE` on Railway
- [ ] **Persistent storage:** Database volumes mounted for SQLite-backed services
- [ ] **Backups:** Regular backup of `/app/data` volumes and SQLite databases
- [ ] **Webhook security:** `WEBHOOK_SECRET` set for signed webhook payloads
- [ ] **Non-root user:** Docker containers running as non-root (bots use `bot:bot`)
- [ ] **Resource limits:** CPU/memory limits set per container in production

### Security Hardening

- [ ] Rotate bot tokens and API keys regularly
- [ ] Use read-only file systems where possible (`--read-only` Docker flag)
- [ ] No `VOLUME` keywords in Dockerfiles for Railway (use Railway Volumes)
- [ ] Keep base images updated (`node:20-alpine`, `node:22-alpine`)
- [ ] Scan images for vulnerabilities (`docker scout`, `trivy`)
- [ ] Never expose private keys — use env vars or secrets managers
- [ ] Set file permissions `0600` for any keypair files

---

## RPC Provider Recommendations

| Provider | Free Tier | Paid Plans | WebSocket | Best For |
|----------|-----------|------------|-----------|----------|
| [Helius](https://helius.dev) | 100K req/day | From $49/mo | ✅ | General Solana development |
| [Alchemy](https://alchemy.com) | 300M CU/mo | From $49/mo | ✅ | Multi-chain projects |
| [QuickNode](https://quicknode.com) | 50M credits | From $49/mo | ✅ | Low-latency trading |
| [Triton](https://triton.one) | — | Custom | ✅ | High-throughput production |

### RPC Tips

- **Always use paid RPC** for production — public endpoints throttle aggressively
- **Use WebSocket** (`SOLANA_WS_URL`) for real-time monitoring instead of polling
- **Set fallback RPCs** (`SOLANA_RPC_URLS`) for automatic failover on 429/5xx errors
- **Batch RPC calls** with `getMultipleAccountsInfo` where possible
- See [RPC Best Practices](./rpc-best-practices.md) for detailed optimization

