## Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

| Problem | Cause | Solution |
|---------|-------|----------|
| Bot not responding | Invalid `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` | Verify token with `curl https://api.telegram.org/bot<TOKEN>/getMe` |
| WebSocket disconnects | Public RPC rate limit | Use a paid RPC provider with WebSocket support |
| `canvas` install fails | Missing native libraries | Install `cairo-dev pango-dev jpeg-dev giflib-dev` on Alpine |
| Railway build fails on VOLUME | Railway doesn't allow VOLUME in Dockerfiles | Use Railway Volumes instead |
| High memory usage | SQLite WAL files growing | Set `PRAGMA journal_mode=DELETE` or increase memory limit |
| 429 errors from RPC | Rate limiting | Set `SOLANA_RPC_URLS` with multiple endpoints for failover |
| Stale data in bot | Polling interval too high | Reduce `POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS` or switch to WebSocket |
| Docker image too large | Dev dependencies included | Ensure multi-stage build with `npm ci --omit=dev` |
| swarm-bot build fails | Missing root SDK | Build from repo root: `docker build -f swarm-bot/Dockerfile .` |

### Logs

```bash
# Docker
docker logs -f pump-telegram-bot

# Railway
railway logs

# Node.js (increase verbosity)
LOG_LEVEL=debug node dist/index.js
```

